Error is non recoverable. We can't recover from an error and programme can't handle it.

                                                                       (Hierarchy)

                                                                        Object (it's an super class)
                                                                           |
                                                                           |
                                                                        Throwable (Inherit the super object class)
                                                                            |
                                                                            |
                                1. Errors                                                                               2. Exceptions
                                                                                                                             |
                                                                                                                             |
                                                                                                                         1. Checked
                                                                                                                         2. Un checked

1. Checked: They are checked during compile time. Example: File not found Exception
2. Un-checked: They are checked during runtime. Example: NPE, I/O Exception, ArithmeticException: / by zero

We have five keywords:
1. try
2. catch
3. finally
4. throw: while we are throwing an exception
5. throws: used to declare an exception